nts1.d: Annabel Fraser is a lover of music first and foremost. Not genres. Tune in for her monthly 2 hour show…
Asheville, NC indie rockers Wednesday serve up an hour of selections running the gamut of guitar music, from Polvo to Lucinda Williams.

Two hours of leftfield dance and beyond every month from AD 93 boss Tasker and guests.
Old 88 Transition shows available on the archive.
Blood Orange links up with Portuguese singer-songwriter Erika De Casier to play some of their current favourites.

nts1.n: KRISTIN KONTROL PRESENTS: OUT OF VOGUE (R)
nts1.d: Former frontwoman of rock outfit Dum Dum Girls eschews the pseudonym with her new solo project, Kristin Kontrol. Newly relocated to LA, Kristin delivers a monthly mix of expansive and hypnotic sounds: one part Durutti Column to two parts Alice Coltrane.

Liquid Mirror is the aural exploration of all intersections of ethereality with musician and artist Olive Kimoto. Interpreted eclectically, the monthly broadcast ranges from shoegaze and dream pop, to electronic and experimental.

nts1.d: Inspired by Quinceñera parties in the hills of Mexico and beyond & rooted in partying as a form of immigrant resistance. La Cosecha was started by XOLO. Playing all Spanish, all vinyl norteñias, corridos, rancheras, cumbia and banda classics. Xolo's aim is to bring this music to a new generation.

nts2.d:
quiet moments, bliss, ease, memory
showing gratitude for the little things and keeping in mind that theres still a chance for peace. some things are worth fighting for! gotta remember that. these songs make me keep going.

nts2.n: WHEN THE SKY WAS WHOLE W/ SLUMP
nts2.d: Slower jams and B-Sides. Sauntering across the landscape.

Everyone knows peace when they feel it: harmony, tranquility, love. But getting there can take work. That means care and respect for others, a lot of fearlessness, even some self-sacrifice. Done right, though, it’s a labor of joy. Because all life is precious (ignore the haters), and because together we will win.

nts2.n: The weight of dust w/ auds
nts2.d:
The afternoon sun soaks up the remaining moody puddles
the corner of her mouth starts to gleam
Grandma turns on her dusty jukebox stereo -
Then,
Her chest flutters to space.

Recorded in the effortless charm of a peaceful lil garden in Taormina, Sicily. With my grandma. 
Recalling the following; the lovely Ionian Sea staring up at me. The ocean looking so still, gleaming with sweet sparkles.
I’m looking forward though, to sitting on my warm front porch back home, and letting my heart flutter to space !
I hope these songs can make your heart flutter too.
Lots of love 
Audrey <3

The freedom to dance, wander or be still. To be reminded of home, loved
ones and moments of true calm. These songs were listened to with a cat on
my lap, on a walk in the sun, sitting at the park and looking at ducks.
Peace comes from within but I hope this mix meets you on the way there.

Peace is indeed can be found anywhere if we search for it although sometimes it seems a bit impossible for the world so in this mix the search is for inner peace with a touch of sadness and joy through jazz, ambient, some folky guitar tunes… 
It's a journey from a muslim saying, a wish for peace in the first sense of the word for which we crave a lot, to a more vague meaning of peace… 
Hope we find it, alone and all together…

A one take vinyl only mix. This is a lil introspective journey through some of my most personal and intimate records. Songs and artists that, in the natural chaos of life, would ground me. Soul nourishers. Anxiety relievers. 
The image of the cows in a field was taken by me in Armenia this October, where the infinite landscapes resonated with sound waves going through the most serene empty valleys. 
Raw Kernels is a series of vinyl-only mixes that express the complexities of human vulnerabilities. A space where I encourage myself and others to share little delicate, painful, hidden, perhaps even forgotten pieces of themselves, play records that we usually don't have the chance to, due to some social pressure or setting. It is genre defying, complex and cathartic. Raw Kernels focuses on expressing heartfelt connection with music through playful and intricate mixing. My own oasis. 
I hope to transmit a feeling of peace through this medium. I hope you feel it. It's not perfect, it's raw! From TwoFace's lil room with Love. Thank you for listening. :)

nts2.n: We Sing Together to Keep Ourselves Warm W/ Splendore
nts2.d: Modern and sacred choirs, recorded in small villages and grand places of worship. When we choose to sing, we do it to keep warm, to protect one another, to love

A quiet search for peace — within and beyond ourselves. I find it in the sax of Jeff Jones, guitars drifting through other worlds, in Talos’ ethereal voice, in thunder and crickets recorded by Kokubo Takashi — moments where inner peace softly echoes outward, gently stirring change.

nts2.n: SERENITY IN REFLECTION W/ PEACEKEEPER RADIO
nts2.d: A reflection on PEACEKEEPER RADIO, a peace-themed mix series I've run for the past three years. Featuring tracks from past collaborators alongside songs that offered clarity in creative uncertainty, it explores how peace emerges through stillness, shared sound and collective practice.

This mix is my auditory representation of the afterlife - a place where one finds true peace. Including ethereal voices, dreamy pads and long, layered ambient tracks, enjoy this dreamlike recording where familiarity and weirdness and everyday logic does not apply.
an attempt at a playlist for and about peace—an offering, as it so often is; not merely an absence of war, but a possibility, a very personal proposition, something that can also hold power, softly.

“Mentors are everywhere”, I thought while chatting to a taxi driver many years ago. In the quest for peace with yourself, music acts as a channel to emotions, wisdom and discoveries. In some weird way, music is that never-ending depository of mentors. This mixtape is a directional journey across high and lows and ultimately, acceptance and hope.

There’s a kind of stillness that appears suddenly, like a flash revealing what I had overlooked. As soon as I reach it, it seems to dissolve, yet it keeps shaping the way I listen to the world. In that space where time loosens and sounds lose their names, I looked for a calm that wasn’t escape but presence. This mix was born after a period of relentless noise, when I rediscovered the relief of silence and the gratitude for every fragment of peace regained.

subtle.d: Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
Hailing from Belfast but making moves in Nottingham, Nikki O is a DJ and radio presenter whose sets blend 4/4 rhythms, breakbeats, and the bassier side of techno.
